Durban - A suspect believed to be involved in the murder and decapitation of a woman whose body was found in a nature reserve in Glenwood has been arrested. According to police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbhele. “On 23 January 2018, at 14:30, the body of a woman in her 30s was found by a passer-by in the bushes at Pigeon Valley. On police arrival at the scene, the body was found half naked and some body parts including the head were missing,” Mbhele said. A case of murder was opened she said. On Monday police with the assistance of the community, caught a 32 year old- suspect. He was detained at Umbilo police station. After interrogation the suspect gave them information leading to the discovery of the woman’s head and finger. The suspect is set to appear in the Durban magistrates court soon, Mbhele said. The arrest was welcomed by  Acting Provincial Commissioner, Major General Bheki Langa. “We will ensure that we do everything within our control to ensure that the suspect is placed before a competent court so that he can account for his actions. We appreciated the commitment shown by the members of the community in fighting crime in our province,” he said. Daily News 